00:36:22.580 --> 00:36:25.570
most of the population has
supported a national health

00:36:25.570 --> 00:36:30.260
care system, the kind
that other countries have.

00:36:30.260 --> 00:36:32.690
Which is pretty remarkable,
because nobody publicly

00:36:32.690 --> 00:36:34.110
advocates it.

00:36:34.110 --> 00:36:39.280
When Obama put through
the Affordable Care Act,

00:36:39.280 --> 00:36:43.340
at the time,
initially, there was

00:36:43.340 --> 00:36:45.740
what was called a
public option, which

00:36:45.740 --> 00:36:50.060
means you could choose
to have essentially

00:36:50.060 --> 00:36:53.450
Medicare, national health care.

00:36:53.450 --> 00:36:55.070
Almost two thirds
of the population

00:36:55.070 --> 00:36:56.900
favored it, even
though there was

00:36:56.900 --> 00:36:59.420
no public articulated
support for it.

00:36:59.420 --> 00:37:01.950
It was dropped, of
course, without comment.

00:37:01.950 --> 00:37:05.855
You go back a little farther,
say to the Reagan years,

00:37:05.855 --> 00:37:11.000
it turned out that about
70% of the population

00:37:11.000 --> 00:37:14.750
thought that guaranteed
health care should

00:37:14.750 --> 00:37:19.570
be in the Constitution,
because it's an obvious right.

00:37:19.570 --> 00:37:24.290
And about 40% thought it
already was in the Constitution.

00:37:24.290 --> 00:37:27.300
The Constitution is just
some holy writ, which

00:37:27.300 --> 00:37:29.090
has everything good in it.

00:37:29.090 --> 00:37:32.000
So it must have had
guaranteed health care,

00:37:32.000 --> 00:37:33.740
because it's so obvious.

00:37:33.740 --> 00:37:35.390
That's the public.

00:37:35.390 --> 00:37:38.300
Of course, it's not the elites.

00:37:38.300 --> 00:37:39.680
It's not the media.

00:37:39.680 --> 00:37:43.100
It's not the elite discourse.

00:37:43.100 --> 00:37:47.300
In fact, whenever the
possibility is mentioned,

00:37:47.300 --> 00:37:51.410
it's called politically
impossible or lacking

00:37:51.410 --> 00:37:54.170
political support,
which is accurate

00:37:54.170 --> 00:37:57.350
if by political support
you mean the pharmaceutical

00:37:57.350 --> 00:38:00.050
corporations, and the
insurance companies, and so on.

00:38:00.050 --> 00:38:01.780
Yeah, they don't support it.

00:38:01.780 --> 00:38:05.840
And the way our democracy
works, that's political support.

00:38:05.840 --> 00:38:07.920
But the public is there.

00:38:07.920 --> 00:38:09.745
And is it educated?

00:38:09.745 --> 00:38:12.610
I mean, where do people
get these ideas from?

00:38:12.610 --> 00:38:14.060
Take say the Vietnam War.

00:38:14.060 --> 00:38:18.620
That's a very, very
interesting, revealing situation

00:38:18.620 --> 00:38:20.870
at the end of the Vietnam War.

00:38:20.870 --> 00:38:23.960
When the Vietnam
War ended in 1975,

00:38:23.960 --> 00:38:28.550
every famous person had to
make a statement about it.

00:38:28.550 --> 00:38:31.940
There's a ton of material
about looking back

00:38:31.940 --> 00:38:35.310
at the Vietnam War, what
did it mean, and so on.

00:38:35.310 --> 00:38:36.530
And there was a spectrum.

00:38:36.530 --> 00:38:37.544
I've written about it.

00:38:37.544 --> 00:38:38.210
Went through it.

00:38:38.210 --> 00:38:39.660
There's a spectrum.

00:38:39.660 --> 00:38:45.710
At one end it said it was a
noble cause, if we'd fought

00:38:45.710 --> 00:38:48.380
harder, we could have won.

00:38:48.380 --> 00:38:50.540
We have to honor the effort.

00:38:50.540 --> 00:38:52.760
Obama agrees with this.

00:38:52.760 --> 00:38:55.170
That's the hawkish end.

00:38:55.170 --> 00:39:00.450
Then you go over to what's
called the left, you know,

00:39:00.450 --> 00:39:02.250
the critical end.

00:39:02.250 --> 00:39:05.040
And people, like
say, Anthony Lewis,

00:39:05.040 --> 00:39:08.610
who was one of the most
harshest critics of the war,

00:39:08.610 --> 00:39:10.980
way out on the left,
he wrote an article

00:39:10.980 --> 00:39:13.740
in which he said the
war, and I'm quoting,

00:39:13.740 --> 00:39:18.840
"The war began with blundering
efforts to do good."

00:39:18.840 --> 00:39:21.190
Notice that that's an axiom.

00:39:21.190 --> 00:39:23.910
You don't have to give
evidence for that.

00:39:23.910 --> 00:39:27.240
If we did it, it was
efforts to do good

00:39:27.240 --> 00:39:31.770
by definition, on the left,
what's called the left.

00:39:31.770 --> 00:39:33.950
Blundering, because
it didn't work.

00:39:33.950 --> 00:39:37.320
So it began with blundering
efforts to do good.

00:39:37.320 --> 00:39:43.210
But by 1969, it had become
clear that it was a disaster.

00:39:43.210 --> 00:39:46.500
We couldn't bring
democracy to Vietnam

00:39:46.500 --> 00:39:49.600
at a cost acceptable
to ourselves.

00:39:49.600 --> 00:39:53.364
That's the critical end, OK?

00:39:53.364 --> 00:39:54.780
You don't have to
give an argument

00:39:54.780 --> 00:39:56.550
to say we're trying
to bring democracy.

00:39:56.550 --> 00:39:57.880
That's also an axiom.

00:39:57.880 --> 00:40:00.930
That's kind of a principle
you don't question,

00:40:00.930 --> 00:40:03.234
it's 2 plus 2 equals 4.

00:40:03.234 --> 00:40:04.650
Well, at the very
same time, there

00:40:04.650 --> 00:40:07.515
were polls taken
among the public.

00:40:07.515 --> 00:40:09.740
And what did they find?

00:40:09.740 --> 00:40:12.930
They found that around
70% of the public

00:40:12.930 --> 00:40:15.630
said the war was
not a mistake, it

00:40:15.630 --> 00:40:19.070
was fundamentally
and morally wrong.

00:40:19.070 --> 00:40:21.540
And that went on as
long as the polls were

00:40:21.540 --> 00:40:24.670
taken until the early '80s.

00:40:24.670 --> 00:40:29.250
Now the people, who
were running the polls,

00:40:29.250 --> 00:40:34.300
liberal, academic,
political scientists,

00:40:34.300 --> 00:40:37.070
he did comment on these results.

00:40:37.070 --> 00:40:41.040
And he said, well, what it means
is that people were opposed

00:40:41.040 --> 00:40:43.186
to American soldiers dying.

00:40:43.186 --> 00:40:46.650
OK, maybe that's what it meant.

00:40:46.650 --> 00:40:49.080
Maybe it meant they thought
it was fundamentally

00:40:49.080 --> 00:40:51.360
wrong and immoral as they said.

00:40:51.360 --> 00:40:54.340
But that concept is just
kind of inconceivable.

00:40:56.990 --> 00:40:58.190
But that's the public.

00:40:58.190 --> 00:41:00.870
Were they educated?

00:41:00.870 --> 00:41:03.610
