can, like any part of science,

00:45:05.070 --> 00:45:08.000
can go in to
different directions.

00:45:08.000 --> 00:45:14.310
It can direct itself towards
some engineering application,

00:45:14.310 --> 00:45:16.800
which may or may not be useful.

00:45:16.800 --> 00:45:19.050
Or it can go into trying
to understand something

00:45:19.050 --> 00:45:20.560
about the world.

00:45:20.560 --> 00:45:22.650
Those are the choices.

00:45:22.650 --> 00:45:26.570
So take, say, the work that
happens to interest me most,

00:45:26.570 --> 00:45:28.500
[INAUDIBLE] language.

00:45:28.500 --> 00:45:33.270
One thrust is
trying to understand

00:45:33.270 --> 00:45:35.490
how it is that we
can, for example, do

00:45:35.490 --> 00:45:37.260
what we're now doing.

00:45:37.260 --> 00:45:38.730
What lies behind that?

00:45:38.730 --> 00:45:41.770
What are the mental operations?

00:45:41.770 --> 00:45:43.120
Or what are the principles?

00:45:43.120 --> 00:45:44.940
How's it acquired, and so on?

00:45:44.940 --> 00:45:47.560
OK, that's one domain.

00:45:47.560 --> 00:45:50.910
Another domain is how
can we get something

00:45:50.910 --> 00:45:56.580
that's useful to give a
kind of a rough translation

00:45:56.580 --> 00:46:03.300
