00:46:57.830 --> 00:46:59.780
I'd love to unpack
that a little bit.

00:46:59.780 --> 00:47:01.800
Where would you like to see--

00:47:01.800 --> 00:47:04.980
how would you like to
see AI research tackle

00:47:04.980 --> 00:47:07.620
these types of deeper
understanding problems?

00:47:07.620 --> 00:47:12.420
NOAM CHOMSKY: Whenever you
learn something in the sciences,

00:47:12.420 --> 00:47:15.260
what immediately
happens is you discover

00:47:15.260 --> 00:47:19.110
there's a mass of new
things, which I never noticed

00:47:19.110 --> 00:47:21.860
before that I don't understand.

00:47:21.860 --> 00:47:24.890
Scientific research is kind
of like mountain climbing.

00:47:24.890 --> 00:47:29.160
You think that that peak
over there is the top,

00:47:29.160 --> 00:47:31.700
but when you get there,
you find, wait a minute,

00:47:31.700 --> 00:47:35.220
turns out there's other peaks
that you didn't notice before.

00:47:35.220 --> 00:47:39.170
Well, that's where
scientific research has gone.

00:47:39.170 --> 00:47:46.850
I mean, take what interests
me, human cognitive capacity,

00:47:46.850 --> 00:47:50.330
which is an astonishing fact
that humans are absolutely

00:47:50.330 --> 00:47:56.210
unique in the organic world in
an enormous number of respects.

00:47:56.210 --> 00:48:01.040
Humans are not that old
in evolutionary terms,

00:48:01.040 --> 00:48:03.290
about 200,000 years.

00:48:03.290 --> 00:48:07.520
So something happened
around 200,000 years ago,

00:48:07.520 --> 00:48:13.330
plus or minus, which created
an entirely new organism, which

00:48:13.330 --> 00:48:15.980
has what we call
higher intelligence,

00:48:15.980 --> 00:48:19.010
which it is now
using incidentally

00:48:19.010 --> 00:48:20.810
to create something
that would be

00:48:20.810 --> 00:48:23.160
headlines in every newspaper.

00:48:23.160 --> 00:48:29.120
We're using human intelligence
to create a perfect storm.

00:48:29.120 --> 00:48:32.840
Since the Second World
War, human intelligence

00:48:32.840 --> 00:48:40.170
has created means of
suicide, self destruction.

00:48:40.170 --> 00:48:42.110
The first is nuclear weapons.

00:48:42.110 --> 00:48:45.460
The Second World War ended
with the nuclear age.

00:48:45.460 --> 00:48:47.630
It was obvious
right at the time,

00:48:47.630 --> 00:48:49.370
I can tell you of
personal experiences,

00:48:49.370 --> 00:48:52.840
that we had now, human
intelligence had now

00:48:52.840 --> 00:48:56.260
devised the means to
destroy everything.

00:48:56.260 --> 00:48:57.830
That's the nuclear age.

00:48:57.830 --> 00:48:59.960
We've barely survived it.

00:48:59.960 --> 00:49:01.700
It wasn't known
then, but it's now

00:49:01.700 --> 00:49:06.380
known that at the same time,
end of the Second World War,

00:49:06.380 --> 00:49:09.560
we had entered a new
geological epoch, what's

00:49:09.560 --> 00:49:14.510
called the Anthropocene, where
human activities are having

00:49:14.510 --> 00:49:18.830
a severely destructive
impact in the environment.

00:49:18.830 --> 00:49:22.022
Geologists have kind of
debated its inception.

00:49:22.022 --> 00:49:23.605
But they have now
more or less agreed,

00:49:23.605 --> 00:49:25.730
and world geological
organizations

00:49:25.730 --> 00:49:29.090
have agreed on end of
the Second World War.

00:49:29.090 --> 00:49:34.070
So here, we created
two huge sledgehammers

00:49:34.070 --> 00:49:38.270
which are able to destroy us.

00:49:38.270 --> 00:49:43.040
In the 1970's human
intelligence took the next step.

00:49:43.040 --> 00:49:46.910
Let's destroy the means
to protect ourselves.

00:49:46.910 --> 00:49:50.150
That's pretty much what
happened as the new,

00:49:50.150 --> 00:49:55.400
as the period of what was called
regimented capitalism shifted

00:49:55.400 --> 00:49:57.500
to the Neoliberal era.

00:49:57.500 --> 00:50:01.100
The Neoliberal era of
the last generation

00:50:01.100 --> 00:50:06.140
is dedicated in principle
to destroying the only means

00:50:06.140 --> 00:50:08.520
to defend ourselves
from destruction.

00:50:08.520 --> 00:50:10.040
It's not called that.

00:50:10.040 --> 00:50:13.280
What it's called is
shifting decision

00:50:13.280 --> 00:50:18.740
making from public institutions,
which at least in principle

00:50:18.740 --> 00:50:23.570
are under public influence,
to private institutions, which

00:50:23.570 --> 00:50:27.170
are immune from public
control in principle.

00:50:27.170 --> 00:50:29.900
That's called shifting
to the market.

00:50:29.900 --> 00:50:31.760
It's under the
rhetoric of freedom.

00:50:31.760 --> 00:50:33.970
But it just means servitude.

00:50:33.970 --> 00:50:36.380
It means servitude
to unaccountable

00:50:36.380 --> 00:50:38.630
private institutions.

00:50:38.630 --> 00:50:43.220
The rhetoric, those of you who
remember Margaret Thatcher,

00:50:43.220 --> 00:50:47.480
"There is no society,
just individuals."

00:50:47.480 --> 00:50:49.610
An ideal, not a description.

00:50:49.610 --> 00:50:51.920
But she may not have
known it, but she

00:50:51.920 --> 00:50:56.450
was paraphrasing Karl
Marx, who at the period

00:50:56.450 --> 00:51:01.520
of the severe French repression
said the French repression is

00:51:01.520 --> 00:51:06.860
turning society into
a sack of potatoes,

00:51:06.860 --> 00:51:11.350
amorphous class of individuals,
who can't work together,

00:51:11.350 --> 00:51:13.460
who are separated and atomized.

00:51:13.460 --> 00:51:16.100
That's the ideal
of Neoliberalism.

00:51:16.100 --> 00:51:19.280
Let's turn society into
a sack of potatoes.

00:51:19.280 --> 00:51:22.440
Let's eliminate the
institutions that might--

00:51:22.440 --> 00:51:26.840
in which engage,
in that the people

00:51:26.840 --> 00:51:30.410
might get together to try
to deal constructively

00:51:30.410 --> 00:51:31.480
with their problems.

00:51:31.480 --> 00:51:35.780
Let's transfer it into the
hands of unaccountable private

00:51:35.780 --> 00:51:39.980
institutions, which are
devoted in principle to profit

00:51:39.980 --> 00:51:43.010
maximization and
power maximization.

00:51:43.010 --> 00:51:46.130
Of course, that means
undermining democracy.

00:51:46.130 --> 00:51:47.800
That's what's happened.

00:51:47.800 --> 00:51:50.650
That's why we see
what's called--

00:51:50.650 --> 00:51:54.390
it's a bad term, it's called
the populist uprising.

00:51:54.390 --> 00:51:56.230
Nothing populist about it.

00:51:56.230 --> 00:52:02.300
It means an anger, fear,
hatred, discontent, contempt

00:52:02.300 --> 00:52:05.420
for institutions, the
collapse of institutions,

00:52:05.420 --> 00:52:11.100
a direct consequence of the
Neoliberal economic policies,

00:52:11.100 --> 00:52:14.300
which have also led to
stagnation or decline

00:52:14.300 --> 00:52:15.980
for the majority.

00:52:15.980 --> 00:52:19.460
Real wages have actually
declined since 1979

00:52:19.460 --> 00:52:21.730
when the program began.

00:52:21.730 --> 00:52:24.310
All of this is together,
and put it together,

00:52:24.310 --> 00:52:26.920
what you have is
human intelligence

00:52:26.920 --> 00:52:32.420
has created two means
of destroying ourself,

00:52:32.420 --> 00:52:36.280
and it has also been
actively engaged

00:52:36.280 --> 00:52:38.770
in trying to eliminate
the only protection we

00:52:38.770 --> 00:52:40.120
have against them.

00:52:40.120 --> 00:52:42.490
So it's a kind of perfect storm.

00:52:42.490 --> 00:52:44.650
That's what humans have done.

00:52:44.650 --> 00:52:46.160
How did this happen?

00:52:46.160 --> 00:52:47.710
How did we get this way?

00:52:47.710 --> 00:52:50.560
How did we develop
creative capacities

00:52:50.560 --> 00:52:56.680
of a unique kind which have led
to extraordinary achievements?

00:52:56.680 --> 00:53:00.800
OK, these are things we have to
try to understand, all of them.

00:53:00.800 --> 00:53:03.520
And do something about,
not just understand.

00:53:03.520 --> 00:53:06.010
SPEAKER 1: Another question
