00:54:45.490 --> 00:54:48.220
And perhaps without it,
many of those publications

00:54:48.220 --> 00:54:51.490
would be without the funding
required to continue.

00:54:51.490 --> 00:54:52.780
NOAM CHOMSKY: That's not true.

00:54:52.780 --> 00:54:56.020
The period of the freest, most
lively press in the United

00:54:56.020 --> 00:54:59.260
States was probably
in the 19th century,

00:54:59.260 --> 00:55:04.230
when you had a proliferation
of all kinds of newspapers,

00:55:04.230 --> 00:55:07.430
ethnic, working class.

00:55:07.430 --> 00:55:09.490
I mentioned the factory girls.

00:55:09.490 --> 00:55:11.170
There were others.

00:55:11.170 --> 00:55:13.450
What happened in the
late 19th century

00:55:13.450 --> 00:55:17.560
is in England and
the United States,

00:55:17.560 --> 00:55:22.460
which also saw a similar shift
